---
/**
 * GitHub Culture Callout Component
 * 
 * Displays a callout linking to posts about GitHub's culture.
 * This replaces the Jekyll {% include_cached github-culture.html %} tag.
 * Uses Tailwind CSS for styling.
 */
---

<aside class="not-prose my-8 rounded-xl bg-gradient-to-r from-primary/5 via-primary/8 to-primary/5 dark:from-primary/10 dark:via-primary/15 dark:to-primary/10 border border-primary/20 dark:border-primary/30 p-6">
  <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
    <span class="text-2xl shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">📚</span>
    <div>
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mb-1">
        Want to learn more about how GitHub works?
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-3">
        I've written extensively about GitHub's culture, communication patterns, and what it's like to be a GitHubber.
      </p>
      <a
        href="/2021/02/01/what-to-read-before-starting-or-interviewing-at-github/"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-sm font-semibold text-primary dark:text-primary-300 no-underline hover:text-primary-700 dark:hover:text-primary-200 transition-colors duration-200"
      >
        Read the unofficial onboarding guide <span aria-hidden="true">→</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</aside>
